    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; this gap is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending only and the regulatory decision does not require dynamic validation at this stage. All three QoIs pass the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device submission.",
